President  Dilma Rousseff  plans to
appoint former Sao Paulo Mayor Gilberto Kassab to head the
ministry of micro and small businesses once the new ministry has
been created, the Sao Paulo-based weekly Veja reported, without
saying how it obtained the information.  Rousseff, of the Workerâ€™s Party, will also hire Senator
Gabriel Chalita, of the Democratic Brazilian Movement Party, to
work for the ministry of science and technology, the magazine
said, without giving further details. Kassab is a member of the
